SetOption $Intro info [Spirit is an item filter for Path of Exile, made by a long time player primarily for SSF but with an eye towards helping new players learn about the game's intense itemization through play - while maintaining strong customization options for veterans. The support for SSF is a result of a focus on personal usability - a combination of build and context such as AreaLevel and DropLevel - and scarcity rather than economic value - which is still a factor.] # |Welcome to Spirit+|

SetOption $Intro2 info [If anyone's wondering, it's called Spirit because I feel it keeps within GGG's thematic palette more closely than other filters, with more aged and natural tones. The PLUS is because of the update that added this Filterblast customization interface (there was another big update that added the Continue syntax that allows the filter to be as wildly flexible as it is.] # This is an all-in-one item filter, you can play from Twilight Strand to Pinnacle content with the Default preset. However, league to league we see different quantities of different items which can affect the strictness of the filter, so several presets are provided and this customization interface does the rest.

SetOption $Intro3 info [Equipment - Weapons and Armours, Accessories (including Jewels), Flasks, and Special Bases | Treasure - Currency, Gems, Jewels, Recipe Items | Stuff - Maps, Chancing, most League Items, Racing, Hunts, Maps | Oddities - Altered items, Affix Filtering, Corrupt Items, Fishing, Racing, League Items which are altered regular items] # Items in Spirit+ are broken up into several categories for ease of use in filtering. The order of these categories does not reflect their importance or actual filtering order, their function is as groups of customization options, and keep in mind this is WIP so some features may not exist yet and organization is ongoing.

